record_data.record_plain_text: Diamond State Generation Partners, LLC FERC Electric Tariff, Volume No. 1 Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service Diamond State Generation Partners, LLC ( DSGP ) provides Reactive Supply and Voltage from Generation Sources Service ( Reactive Supply Service ) from its generating facility located in New Castle County, Delaware, and interconnected to transmission facilities of Delmarva Power and Light Company. This FERC Electric Tariff, Original Volume No. 1 sets forth DSGP s revenue requirements for the provision of Reactive Supply Service to PJM Interconnection, L.L.C. ( PJM ), as contemplated by Schedule 2 of the PJM Open Access Transmission Tariff. This Tariff shall be effective upon the date authorized by the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission. TOTAL REVENUE REQUIREMENT: The total annual revenue requirement is $45,000.00. The total monthly revenue requirement is $3,750.00.
